WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:04,950
If invisible work is growing and adoption is not, the breakdown is usually in live decisions.

00:05,000 --> 00:09,950
Teams often move faster on content than on feedback clarity in weekly operations. Gamification holds up...

00:10,000 --> 00:14,950
Pick one owner and one metric, then run one weekly checkpoint in the workstream.

00:15,000 --> 00:19,950
Run a one-week pilot, capture evidence from real behavior, then adjust immediately.

00:20,000 --> 00:24,950
This usually improves first-pass quality, cleaner feedback handoffs, and faster team adoption.

00:25,000 --> 00:29,950
Which weekly checkpoint would improve decision quality first?
